The paper deals with approximation algorithms for multi-criteria optimization problems in the context of traveling salesman problems. This involves designing algorithms for cycle cover and graph factor problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper presents randomized approximation schemes, which are often used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for solving optimization problems. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of approximation ratios, which is a common technique in the field of theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
